<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-21-0614 </DOCNO><TEXT>The book is intended as a source of information for general practionersand for medical students doing their practical training. Efficient applicationof imaging methods is explained with great emphasis on practical aspects,concentrating on typical tasks to be solved for adult patients with internaldisease or surgical problems. The material is arranged by various organicsystems of the body. Graded diagnostics for a stepwise approach to thefinal diagnosis is the concept described, and is shown to be of advantageto the patient and in terms of cost and time.</TEXT></DOC>